Vice President Joe Biden expressed his condolences on the passing of Crown Prince Sultan bin Abd al-Aziz of Saudi Arabia. He highlighted the prince's decades-long service to the Saudi people as Minister of Defense and Aviation, as well as his philanthropy efforts in Saudi Arabia, such as funding housing and medical care for those in need and supporting scientific research on water and desertification. Biden also acknowledged the prince's role in strengthening the relationship between the United States and Saudi Arabia, emphasizing their close partnership. He joined President Obama and the entire administration in offering condolences to the royal family and the people of Saudi Arabia.